Nedum Onuoha is wanted by Hull City . The QPR centre-back is one of several players poised to leave should the Loftus Road club go down as they consider streamlining their squad . The 28-year-old has 15 months left on contract and has played regularly under Chris Ramsey . Onuoha was in the starting eleven for the Saturday 's crucial 4-1 win over relegation rivals West Bromwich Albion at the Hawthorns . Nedum Onuoha is being targeted by Hull City but is also interesting Everton and West Ham United . Stoke manager Mark Hughes who signed him for QPR is also interested as are Everton and West Ham . QPR have held talks over a move for Catania defender Nicolas Spolli . The 32-year-old has been on loan at Roma . Hull , meanwhile , are also showing interest in West Bromwich Albion striker Victor Anichebe who is likely to be sold this summer . Victor Anichebe -LRB- centre -RRB- is also being watched by Hull City and could move to the KC Stadium in the summer .